{
  "texts": [
    "We take the 'character' as an example to illustrate the sample construction pipeline, as depicted in Figure 2.",
    "In addition, we provide information on the construction pipeline for samples involving other objects in supplementary Section 1.1.In the first step, we construct image groups for different characters from the DeepFashion dataset [30], in which the same character exhibit identical clothing but different poses and view angles.",
    "We select two images of the same character with varied poses as the main character (e.g., A in Figure 2), along with two another distinct characters as additional characters (e.g., B and C in Figure 2).",
    "Next, we segment each character from the source image using Segment Anything [19].",
    "We combine the main character with each of the two additional characters and place them onto a 512 × 512 mask image with diverse positions and sizes."
  ]
}